The paper proposes a novel framework for deep multi-view clustering, which involves learning multiple deep embedded features and clustering assignments simultaneously. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of clustering algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the use of image datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
